annotation.TEXT: It looks like the left edge of the screen is once again the safest place to be.
Whether I want to spin jump or normal jump will mainly depend on where Bowser's fireballs are.
Oh, Satori just sped up.
That's two. I wonder if his stomps will stun me if I'm on the ground now...
Oh, man. Satori's pooping out Chucks!
Satori just sped up there, which means...
D'oh! I somehow missed the jump button there. Oh, well. Now I can move forward without worrying about wasting a power up.
Oh, I guess I'm at the top of the level, so Aya must be just ahead...
Lucky bomb drop there!
And... I think that's all of those point items I can possibly reach. (Well, maybe I could eke out a couple more, but most of what's left there looks unreachable.)
D'oh I missed! ...Oh, come on! Land on something!
That might just work...
I think I'll leave this map music playing for just a little while longer.
Anything to the right? Nope, guess not. Anything to the left? Didn't have enough time to check. Oh, well.
Okay, I'm back to where I was.
Wow, I'm surprised that fireball didn't hit me.
Oh, my... That's... really creepy...
I still don't think that's how this song is normally supposed to loop. Yeah, maybe Touhou music ports in this hack could use some improvement...
...Hahaha! What, is Mario mentally preparing for his next trip to an Italian restaurant?

And that's it! With the completion of that level, the path to the warp star is now complete! However, first I should go back to the Hakurei Shrine to... Umm... Wait, did I actually finish that battle at full health?
Alright, are we ready... to warp?
Uh, oh. Mario's daydreaming about pasta again... And, since Satori's a mind-reader, she might get hungry just listening to him mention all this food...
Maybe I was paying more attention than you thought.
What, really? The Thwomp boss? Man, this guy is so overused. However, he makes perfect sense here, and the floor spikes will make this more challenging.
Okay, that's one hit, finally.
Let's-a-go!
I would guess so.
Bam! There you go! I just have to toss the orbs at her! (I wonder if stomping her would work too, but I'm not going to bother trying to do that...)
And then I just climb back up and fall again for some more!
Well, depending on what I encounter beyond the warp star, I might end up coming back here to make more donations in the future...
Oh, what's this? Is she doing what she does for the second half of her fight in Subterranean Animism?
Okay, now if I fall here... POINT ITEMS!!!
Okay, stop falling down already.
Oh, man. There's a bunch of point items up there! How can I reach them? Probably from above.
Alright, looks like this level is going to be based on Mountain of Faith's fourth stage.
Okay, so it's mid-boss time, but how do I reach her? With well-timed bullet hops? No, actually, the game's giving me Goomba orbs, so...
Whoa, I shouldn't break all of those blocks until I get all of the point items above them.
Hello, and welcome back to Touhou Mario! Now it's time for Peaceful waterwall... or Peacefull waterfall... or Peaceful waterful... or however Peaceful waterfall is supposed to be spelled...
BGM: TH10 - Stage 4 - Fall of Fall ~ Autumnal Waterfall
Alright, got him! Who's the next opponent from Mario's past?
Anything to the right? Doesn't look like it.
Die, Hammer Guy!
Alright, so it took ten hits to defeat Momiji, and that was the only pattern she had, which makes sense.
Anyway, it appears that next time, I'll be entering this nightmare fuel portrait of... Flandre... I think. (That is Flandre, right?)
BGM: TH11 - Satori Maiden ~ 3rd eye
Fortunately, I can jump high enough to stomp Satori without assistance, so it's not absolutely necessary to bullet hop or Chuck hop to reach her.
Well, I cloned one note block...
Umm... Do I just kill the guy or concentrate on the block factory? Decisions, decisions...

I just experienced a weird glitch while annotating here. I clicked "Add annotation" during this sped up part, and it suddenly jumped to 3:26 in the video, the video quality dropped to 240p, and the 360p option that I'm normally on became grayed out. I had to refresh the page to fix it. What was up with that?
Okay, I'm glad I was able to reach that one point item from the slope...
I like how the Thwomp gets a Bob-omb image on him as he's smashing down.
Also, it looks like I'm relatively safe in the lower-left corner. I just have to deal with an occasional bullet from the upper-right, and the orbs too, of course.
And, the next stomp after the speed up ended the phase, which I completed perfectly!
Okay, a breakable floor, and... AAAAAaaaaahhhhh!!!!!
Whoops! Aiming upward would help.
Wait, don't be getting all reckless yet. I think I might be able to target her from behind without getting hit by the shuriken...

And now, for the third fight from Mario's past, we have Bowser. Also, there's a spell circle shooting a few bullets (thankfully no evil homing bullets), and Satori herself. I guess I gotta stomp Satori a bunch of times while avoiding everything else.
Yep, this is my strategy, and I'm sticking with it, because it's working.
Oh, come on! That didn't hit him?
Yeah, I should speed up some of this footage.
Argh, this is suddenly going downhill fast!
Yes! I perfectly captured the spell card, Recollection "Classic Bowser"! And, it appears that's the end of the boss fight. Well, that certainly was interesting.
Oh, hey there, Satori. How's it going? I wasn't expecting to see you here.
Also, yes, in case you forgot, Chucks in this hack only take two stomps to defeat.
Man, all of a sudden, I'm having trouble getting an attack off...
Yep, looks like it, and now I've gotta battle Mouser! This is actually a pretty cool idea!
Does Luigi's Mansion have such a big hole?
Yeah, I figured those would be note blocks. Hey, maybe I can get a block factory going with this orb!
Umm... Where did that Hammer Bro. come from, and why wasn't he there when I passed through there a moment ago?
Whoa, I had no idea there was a screen transition there. Oh, hey there, Momiji. How's it going?
D'oh. I gotta be careful not to lose orbs to the bullets. Also, how many hits does Momiji take?
So, when did Mario become Marv from Home Alone 2?
Shouldn't that say "Dirty" instead of "Dirt"?
Unfortunately, thanks to those shuriken, I'm not getting a perfect here.
Yeah, trying to avoid collecting these power ups was restricting my movement too much.
Hmm... These clearly act like winged orbs (paragoombas), but I wonder why their wings aren't visible here...
Umm... Is that how this song normally loops?
Alright. Crisis averted. (Well, it wasn't really a crisis, but whatever.) Also, it seems that I've revealed that the next block is a note block.
Pfft. A fat lot of help that Bob-omb will be down there...
Um, what?
The spikes here certainly make this battle more challenging, and I don't want to move forward and collect that power up until I've taken a hit.

This just seems like all kinds of weird, but whatever. I should be able to handle this by mostly staking out the lower-left corner... Assuming Satori doesn't start shooting evil homing bullets at me or something...
FLAWLESS VICTORY
Oh, but I can hit Mouser that way!
Hmm... Looks like this hack used the wrong dirt tile in some places...
D'oh, well that attempt to KO the Hammer Bro. failed... But, I could try tossing the Goomba orb at him.
Okay, I'm wasting too much time here and I don't want to risk taking any dumb hits, so Hammer Duder, meet Mr. Orb!
LOL at dumb spike hit which is irrelevant.
To be continued...

So, if this level has the Momiji mid-boss, how come Frozen forest didn't have a Daiyousei mid-boss, and The Scarlet Devil didn't have a Koakuma mid-boss during Patchouli's segment? (Well, The Scarlet Devil was long enough as it is...)
Whoa! I wasn't expecting that! So, apparently, some of these blocks are actually note blocks in disguise...
Of course, it's a guessing game as to which blocks are note blocks until they've been checked.
Yes, I did! I do not need to make any donations this time! ...Umm... Sorry, Reimu.
Well, that sucked. Now I gotta climb all the way back up to where I was. If that happens again, expect some sped up footage and perhaps some Yakety Sax.
Yep, they stun me!
I don't know if it's within Mario's capability to ever stop thinking about pasta...
Meh, can't really climb up that way.
Oh, man. She sped up again! But, does this mean the next hit ends it? ...It does!
